I'm building a server which serves file content (ie; it's purpose is just to serve the file). When the network is interrupted,
i) If the connection is alive, the browser could continue downloading the file content ii) If the connection is not alive, chrome just marks the file as "successfully downloaded" though it is not.
httpsconnection .setRequestProperty( "connection" , "keep-alive" ); httpsconnection .setRequestProperty( "content-length" , "0" );
httpsconnection .setConnectTimeout(4000);
httpsconnection .setReadTimeout(30000);
While downloading files from other websites i could see them as "Failure - Network Interrupted". I'm setting these request properties. Am I missing anything? Please help me with this.
Whereas other browser like firefox doesn't mark them as paused automatically.
